Given a TodoAction with a Scan covering all spec and marker IDs, the algorithm must produce a todo per linked edge where the current hash differs from the baseline and no resolution entry matches the current hashes. Edges where both sides are unchanged must produce no todo. Edges with a matching resolution entry must produce no todo. When a spec or marker has been deleted (scan hash is empty string), the todo must set the corresponding Deleted flag. The algorithm also emits ref-graph todos: TodoRefChain for specs transitively connected (via the undirected ref graph) to a changed spec with no covering ref resolution, TodoCascade for markers linked to a ref-chain-drifted spec, TodoRefAdded and TodoRefRemoved for edges that appear in only one of the baseline or scan, and TodoBrokenRef for refs whose target ID does not resolve to a spec. The returned EvaluatedState propagates Refs and RefResolutions unchanged. See principles.friction.